---
import Layout from '../layouts/Base.astro';

// CTO review B4 — hide placeholder "Praise" until the first real ARC endorsement lands.
const SHOW_PRAISE = false;
---

<Layout title="The Lund Covenant — Greg Maxfield" description="A novel of the American West. When Gill Lund returns to Castle Dale, Utah after his father's death, he intends to stay three days." image="/images/og-image.png">

<!-- BOOK HERO -->
<section class="book-page-hero">
  <img
    src="/images/tlc-cover-front.jpg"
    alt="The Lund Covenant by Greg Maxfield"
    width="320"
    height="480"
    transition:name="tlc-cover"
    transition:animate="initial"
  />
  <h1>The Lund Covenant</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">A Novel</p>
  <p class="byline">by Greg Maxfield</p>
  <p class="release-badge" style="display:inline-block; margin:0.75rem 0 1rem; padding:0.4rem 1rem; border:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.15); border-radius:999px; font-size:0.95rem; letter-spacing:0.04em; text-transform:uppercase;">Coming June 30, 2026</p>
  <div class="buy-buttons">
    <a href="#early-access" class="btn btn-primary">Join the Launch List</a>
    <a href="#order" class="btn btn-secondary">Order Your Copy</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FULL BLURB -->
<section class="book-page-blurb reveal">
  <p>
    When Gill Lund returns to Castle Dale, Utah after his father's death, he intends to stay three days.
    Long enough to bury the man, settle the estate, and go back to the life he built on the other side
    of twelve years and a lot of open country.
  </p>
  <p>The town has other plans.</p>
  <p>
    His father — quiet, stubborn, not a man who explained himself — had been driving into the desert
    at odd hours, tending water caches hidden in the San Rafael Swell. Desert travelers in desperate need.
    Small mercies, unmarked and unannounced. Until someone found them and destroyed them, methodically,
    with bleach and a serrated blade.
  </p>
  <p>
    The evidence leads somewhere no one in Castle Dale wants to look. And the more Gill asks, the more
    he understands that his father's silence wasn't indifference — it was the posture of a man who had
    already paid the cost of speaking plainly in a small town, and who kept doing the work anyway.
  </p>
  <p>
    Gill is a photojournalist. He knows how to document things. What he doesn't know yet is whether
    he's willing to be part of the story.
  </p>
</section>

<!-- ABOUT THE BOOK -->
<section class="book-page-about">
  <div class="inner reveal">
    <h2>About the Book</h2>
    <p>
      <em>The Lund Covenant</em> is a novel about moral inheritance — the obligations that place imposes,
      the cost of bearing witness, and what changes when a man decides to stay. Set in the high desert of
      Emery County, Utah, it follows a photojournalist's reckoning with a small Mormon community fracturing
      under the weight of a secret that was never meant to surface.
    </p>
    <p>
      Literary fiction with a suspense spine, <em>The Lund Covenant</em> belongs on the shelf next to
      Kent Haruf's <em>Plainsong</em>, Ron Rash's <em>Serena</em>, Marilynne Robinson's <em>Gilead</em>,
      and Paulette Jiles's <em>News of the World</em>.
    </p>
    <p style="color:var(--color-text-light); font-size:0.95rem; margin-top:1.5rem;">
      ~82,000 words &middot; Paperback &amp; Ebook &middot; June 30, 2026
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ENDORSEMENTS — hidden until real ARC quotes land (CTO review B4); flip SHOW_PRAISE to restore -->
{SHOW_PRAISE && (
<section class="endorsements reveal">
  <h2>Praise</h2>
  <div class="endorsement-slot">
    <p>"Endorsement quote placeholder — to be populated from ARC reviews."</p>
    <p><strong>— Reviewer Name, Source</strong></p>
  </div>
  <div class="endorsement-slot">
    <p>"Endorsement quote placeholder — to be populated from ARC reviews."</p>
    <p><strong>— Reviewer Name, Source</strong></p>
  </div>
  <div class="endorsement-slot">
    <p>"Endorsement quote placeholder — to be populated from ARC reviews."</p>
    <p><strong>— Reviewer Name, Source</strong></p>
  </div>
</section>
)}

<!-- ORDER YOUR COPY -->
<section id="order" style="text-align:center; padding:2rem 1.5rem 1rem;">
  <h2 style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Order Your Copy</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Available June 30, 2026 — pre-order now.</p>
  <div class="buy-buttons">
    <!-- TODO replace href="#" with live listings when IngramSpark / Goodreads links are created -->
    <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0H1XQCBPH" class="btn btn-primary">Pre-Order on Amazon</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-secondary" aria-disabled="true">IngramSpark / Bookstores</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-ghost" aria-disabled="true">Add on Goodreads</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- EARLY ACCESS / LAUNCH LIST (CTO review F1 — live Kit capture, ported from homepage) -->
<section id="early-access" class="subscribe-section">
  <div class="container content-narrow reveal" style="text-align:center;">
    <h2>Get Early Access</h2>
    <p>Join the launch list for <em>The Lund Covenant</em>. Receive the opening chapters in advance, plus cover reveal and pre-order news.</p>

    <form id="kit-signup-form" class="kit-form" aria-label="Launch list signup">
      <div class="kit-form-fields">
        <input
          type="text"
          name="first_name"
          placeholder="First name"
          class="kit-input"
          autocomplete="given-name"
        />
        <input
          type="email"
          name="email"
          placeholder="Email address"
          class="kit-input"
          required
          autocomplete="email"
        />
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary kit-submit">
          <span class="kit-submit-text">Join the Launch List</span>
          <span class="kit-submit-loading" style="display:none;">Joining…</span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <p class="kit-form-note">Early chapters, cover reveal, and pre-order news. No spam. Unsubscribe anytime.</p>
    </form>
    <div id="kit-success" class="kit-message kit-success" style="display:none;">
      <p><strong>You're in.</strong> Check your inbox for a confirmation email. Welcome aboard.</p>
    </div>
    <div id="kit-error" class="kit-message kit-error" style="display:none;">
      <p>Something went wrong. Please try again, or email <a href="mailto:greg@gregmaxfield.com" style="color:var(--color-accent);">greg@gregmaxfield.com</a> directly.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- AUTHOR BIO -->
<section class="book-page-bio reveal" style="padding:3rem 1.5rem; text-align:center;">
  <div class="container content-narrow">
    <h2>About the Author</h2>
    <p>
      Greg Maxfield writes literary fiction grounded in the American West. He grew up around Castle Dale, Utah,
      where his family helped settle the Emery County high desert, and his work returns again and again to
      that country — its people, its silences, and the moral weight of place.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
      <a href="/about" class="link-arrow">More from Greg Maxfield &rarr;</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Reveal + Kit form handlers now live in Base.astro (B1 fix). -->

<style>
  /* Kit signup form — ported from homepage pattern (CTO review F1). Styled for dark subscribe-section. */
  .kit-form { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .kit-form-fields {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .kit-input {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 160px;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.2rem;
    border: 2px solid rgba(250,248,245,0.3);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: rgba(250,248,245,0.1);
    color: var(--color-bg);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    transition: border-color var(--transition), background var(--transition);
  }
  .kit-input::placeholder { color: rgba(250,248,245,0.5); }
  .kit-input:focus {
    outline: none;
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    background: rgba(250,248,245,0.15);
  }
  .kit-submit { min-width: 140px; white-space: nowrap; }
  .kit-form-note {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    color: rgba(250,248,245,0.6);
  }
  .kit-message {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
  }
  .kit-success {
    background: rgba(250,248,245,0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(250,248,245,0.25);
  }
  .kit-error {
    background: rgba(200,50,50,0.15);
    border: 1px solid rgba(200,50,50,0.3);
  }
  .kit-message p { margin: 0; font-size: 1rem; }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .kit-form-fields { flex-direction: column; }
    .kit-input, .kit-submit { width: 100%; min-width: auto; }
  }
</style>


</Layout>
